186
00:10:52,686 --> 00:10:54,317
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who are you?</font>

187
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:57,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">Rest, <i>Mama.</i></font>

188
00:10:57,926 --> 00:11:01,092
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm hard on you
because I care, Miguel.</font>

189
00:11:01,095 --> 00:11:03,277
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miguel? Miguel?</font>

190
00:11:06,234 --> 00:11:09,366
<font color="#FFFFFF">What are we going
to do with that boy?</font>

191
00:11:09,369 --> 00:11:13,421
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're right.
That's just what he needs.</font>

192
00:11:37,364 --> 00:11:39,096
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's you. Get in here.</font>

193
00:11:39,099 --> 00:11:42,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, Dante. Hurry up!</font>

194
00:11:42,168 --> 00:11:44,135
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're gonna
get me in trouble, boy.</font>

195
00:11:44,138 --> 00:11:45,720
<font color="#FFFFFF">Someone could hear me.</font>

196
00:11:50,445 --> 00:11:52,409
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wish someone
wanted to hear me.</font>

197
00:11:53,748 --> 00:11:56,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">Other than you. Ew. Okay.</font>

198
00:11:58,318 --> 00:12:00,467
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Perfecto!</i></font>

199
00:12:33,888 --> 00:12:36,453
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>I have to sing.
I have to play!</i></font>

200
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:41,206
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>The music, it's not
just in me, it is me.</i></font>

201
00:12:42,996 --> 00:12:46,113
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>When life gets me down,
I play my guitar.</i></font>

202
00:12:47,033 --> 00:12:49,234
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>The rest of the world
may follow the rules,</i></font>

203
00:12:49,235 --> 00:12:52,119
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>but I must follow my heart.</i></font>

204
00:12:52,505 --> 00:12:54,173
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ugh!</font>

205
00:12:54,174 --> 00:12:56,974
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>You know that feeling like
there's a song in the air and...</i></font>

206
00:12:56,975 --> 00:12:59,092
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>it's playing just for you?</i></font>

207
00:13:02,216 --> 00:13:05,384
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>♪ A feeling so close...</i></font>

208
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:09,702
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>♪ You could
reach out and touch it</i></font>

209
00:13:10,355 --> 00:13:12,222
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>♪ I never knew</i></font>

210
00:13:12,225 --> 00:13:16,376
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>♪ I could want something
so much, but it's true ♪</i></font>

211
00:13:17,331 --> 00:13:18,929
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>You must have faith, sister.</i></font>

212
00:13:18,932 --> 00:13:21,365
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Oh, but,</i> Padre,
<i>he will never listen.</i></font>

213
00:13:21,368 --> 00:13:23,400
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>He will listen. To music.</i></font>

214
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:27,004
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>♪ Only a song,
only a song</i></font>

215
00:13:27,006 --> 00:13:29,690
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>♪ Has the power
to change a heart ♪</i></font>

216
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:36,831
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Never underestimate
the power of music.</i></font>

217
00:13:41,221 --> 00:13:44,556
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>But my father, he will
never give his permission.</i></font>

218
00:13:44,557 --> 00:13:46,191
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>I am done
asking permission.</i></font>

219
00:13:46,192 --> 00:13:49,361
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>When you see your moment, you
mustn't let it pass you by.</i></font>

220
00:13:49,364 --> 00:13:51,261
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>You must seize it!</i></font>

221
00:13:51,264 --> 00:13:52,496
<font color="#FFFFFF">Senor <i>de la Cruz,</i></font>

222
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:55,548
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>what did it take for you
to seize your moment?</i></font>

223
00:13:57,105 --> 00:14:00,005
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>I had to have
faith in my dream.</i></font>

224
00:14:00,008 --> 00:14:01,972
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>No one was going
to hand it to me.</i></font>

225
00:14:01,975 --> 00:14:04,275
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>It was up to me
to reach for that dream.</i></font>

226
00:14:04,278 --> 00:14:06,245
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Grab it tight
and make it come true.</i></font>

227
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:07,861
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>and make it come true.</i></font>

228
00:14:12,386 --> 00:14:16,020
<font color="#FFFFFF">No more hiding, Dante.
I got to seize my moment!</font>

229
00:14:17,192 --> 00:14:20,192
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm gonna play in Mariachi
Plaza if it kills me.</font>

230
00:14:23,565 --> 00:14:27,265
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Dia de los Muertos</i> has begun!</font>

231
00:14:27,268 --> 00:14:30,534
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no. We have to make
a clear path.</font>

232
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:33,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">The petals guide
our ancestors home.</font>

233
00:14:33,172 --> 00:14:35,206
<font color="#FFFFFF">We don't want
their spirits to get lost.</font>

234
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:37,909
<font color="#FFFFFF">We want them to come
and enjoy all the food</font>

235
00:14:37,912 --> 00:14:39,527
<font color="#FFFFFF">and drinks on the <i>ofrenda.</i></font>

236
00:14:40,614 --> 00:14:41,979
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Mama!</i></font>

237
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:43,346
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where should we
put this table?</font>

238
00:14:43,349 --> 00:14:45,049
<font color="#FFFFFF">In the courtyard, <i>mijos.</i></font>

239
00:14:45,052 --> 00:14:46,217
<font color="#FFFFFF">You want it
down by the kitchen?</font>

240
00:14:46,221 --> 00:14:48,620
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Si.</i> Next to the other one.</font>

241
00:14:51,191 --> 00:14:54,159
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Get under! Get under!
- Miguel?</font>

242
00:14:54,162 --> 00:14:57,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">Nothing! <i>Mama, Papa.</i> I...</font>

243
00:14:57,599 --> 00:15:02,466
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miguel, your <i>abuelita</i> had
the most wonderful idea.</font>

244
00:15:02,469 --> 00:15:06,705
<font color="#FFFFFF">We've all decided. It's time
you joined us in the workshop!</font>

245
00:15:06,706 --> 00:15:09,174
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What?
- No more shining shoes.</font>

246
00:15:09,177 --> 00:15:12,110
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll be making them
every day after school.</font>

247
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:15,179
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh! Our Migueli-ti-ti-ti-to</font>

248
00:15:15,182 --> 00:15:17,649
<font color="#FFFFFF">carrying on
the family tradition.</font>

249
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:20,317
<font color="#FFFFFF">And on <i>Dia de los Muertos!</i></font>

250
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:23,120
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your ancestors
will be so proud.</font>

251
00:15:23,123 --> 00:15:26,524
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll craft huaraches
just like your <i>Tia</i> Victoria.</font>

252
00:15:26,528 --> 00:15:29,193
<font color="#FFFFFF">And wingtips
like your <i>Papa</i> Julio.</font>

253
00:15:29,196 --> 00:15:31,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">But what if
I'm no good at making shoes?</font>

254
00:15:31,731 --> 00:15:36,101
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ah, Miguel. You have your
family here to guide you.</font>

255
00:15:36,104 --> 00:15:40,688
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are a Rivera.
And a Rivera is...</font>

256
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:44,241
<font color="#FFFFFF">A shoemaker.
Through and through.</font>

257
00:15:44,244 --> 00:15:47,279
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's my boy!
Berto!</font>

258
00:15:47,282 --> 00:15:50,246
<font color="#FFFFFF">Break out the good stuff.
I want to make a toast.</font>

259
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:03,876
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dante! No, Dante. Stop!</font>

260
00:16:14,142 --> 00:16:17,458
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no, no, no, no! No.</font>

261
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:31,588
<font color="#FFFFFF">De la Cruz's guitar?</font>

262
00:16:31,591 --> 00:16:35,040
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Papa? Papa?</i></font>

263
00:16:36,195 --> 00:16:40,165
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Mama</i> Coco, is your <i>papa</i>
Ernesto de la Cruz?</font>

264
00:16:40,168 --> 00:16:42,801
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Papa! Papa!</i></font>

265
00:16:54,414 --> 00:16:56,548
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Papa! Papa!</i> It's him!</font>

266
00:16:56,551 --> 00:16:58,415
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know who my
great-great-grandfather was.</font>

267
00:16:58,418 --> 00:17:00,452
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miguel, get down
from there.</font>

268
00:17:00,455 --> 00:17:03,221
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Mama</i> Coco's father
was Ernesto de la Cruz!</font>

269
00:17:03,222 --> 00:17:04,521
<font color="#FFFFFF">What are you talking about?</font>

270
00:17:04,525 --> 00:17:06,605
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm gonna be a musician!</font>

271
00:17:08,326 --> 00:17:09,628
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is all this?</font>

272
00:17:09,631 --> 00:17:11,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">You keep secrets
from your own family?</font>

273
00:17:11,731 --> 00:17:14,065
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's all that time
he spends in the plaza.</font>

274
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:15,468
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fills his head
with crazy fantasies.</font>

275
00:17:15,470 --> 00:17:17,068
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's not a fantasy.</font>

276
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:19,336
<font color="#FFFFFF">That man was
Ernesto de la Cruz!</font>

277
00:17:19,337 --> 00:17:21,207
<font color="#FFFFFF">The greatest musician
of all time!</font>

278
00:17:21,209 --> 00:17:22,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">We've never known anything
about this man!</font>

279
00:17:22,742 --> 00:17:26,478
<font color="#FFFFFF">But whoever he was, he still
abandoned his family.</font>

280
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,113
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is no future
for my son.</font>

281
00:17:28,115 --> 00:17:30,650
<font color="#FFFFFF">But, <i>Papa,</i> you said
my family would guide me.</font>

282
00:17:30,652 --> 00:17:33,219
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, de la Cruz
is my family.</font>

283
00:17:33,221 --> 00:17:34,753
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm supposed to play music.</font>

284
00:17:34,756 --> 00:17:37,088
<font color="#FFFFFF">Never! That man's music
was a curse.</font>

285
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:39,090
<font color="#FFFFFF">I will not allow it.</font>

286
00:17:39,093 --> 00:17:40,624
<font color="#FFFFFF">- If you would just let...
- Miguel...</font>

287
00:17:40,625 --> 00:17:42,228
<font color="#FFFFFF">You will listen
to your family.</font>

288
00:17:42,230 --> 00:17:43,527
<font color="#FFFFFF">No more music.</font>

289
00:17:43,528 --> 00:17:46,679
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Just listen to me play!
- End of argument.</font>

290
00:17:48,501 --> 00:17:51,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">You want to end up
like that man? Forgotten?</font>

291
00:17:51,171 --> 00:17:53,573
<font color="#FFFFFF">Left off
your family's <i>ofrenda?</i></font>

292
00:17:53,575 --> 00:17:55,707
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't care if I'm on
some stupid <i>ofrenda.</i></font>

293
00:17:59,546 --> 00:18:00,711
<font color="#FFFFFF">- No!
- <i>Mama!</i></font>

294
00:18:05,420 --> 00:18:09,253
<font color="#FFFFFF">There. No guitar.
No music.</font>

295
00:18:11,526 --> 00:18:16,460
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, come. You'll feel better
after you eat with your family.</font>

296
00:18:16,461 --> 00:18:18,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't want
to be in this family!</font>

297
00:18:18,798 --> 00:18:21,047
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miguel! Miguel!</font>

298
00:18:39,486 --> 00:18:42,354
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want to play in the plaza,
like de la Cruz.</font>

299
00:18:42,355 --> 00:18:43,555
<font color="#FFFFFF">Can I still sign up?</font>

300
00:18:43,557 --> 00:18:45,222
<font color="#FFFFFF">You got an instrument?</font>

301
00:18:45,224 --> 00:18:47,558
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. But if I
can borrow a guitar...</font>

302
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">Musicians got to bring
their own instruments.</font>

303
00:18:49,429 --> 00:18:50,895
<font color="#FFFFFF">You find a guitar, kid,</font>

304
00:18:50,898 --> 00:18:52,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll put you on the list.</font>

305
00:18:54,836 --> 00:18:58,302
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Can I borrow your guitar?
- Sorry, <i>muchacho.</i></font>

306
00:18:58,305 --> 00:19:01,305
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You guys have a spare guitar?
- No.</font>

307
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:03,440
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need a guitar
just for a little bit.</font>

308
00:19:03,442 --> 00:19:06,025
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get out of here, kid.</font>

309
00:19:17,857 --> 00:19:22,208
<font color="#FFFFFF">Great-great-grandfather,
what am I supposed to do?</font>

310
00:19:59,901 --> 00:20:01,398
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no, no, no.</font>

311
00:20:01,401 --> 00:20:04,269
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dante, stop! <i>Callate!</i> Shh!</font>

312
00:20:25,727 --> 00:20:27,240
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm sorry.</font>

313
00:21:03,498 --> 00:21:07,332
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Senor</i> de la Cruz,
please don't be mad.</font>

314
00:21:07,334 --> 00:21:08,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm Miguel.</font>

315
00:21:08,701 --> 00:21:13,286
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your great-great grandson.
I need to borrow this.</font>

316
00:21:16,309 --> 00:21:18,843
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our family thinks
music is a curse.</font>

317
00:21:18,845 --> 00:21:22,746
<font color="#FFFFFF">None of them understand
but I know you would have.</font>

318
00:21:22,748 --> 00:21:25,517
<font color="#FFFFFF">You would have told me
to follow my heart.</font>

319
00:21:25,519 --> 00:21:27,032
<font color="#FFFFFF">To seize my moment!</font>

320
00:21:28,323 --> 00:21:31,324
<font color="#FFFFFF">So, if it's
all right with you,</font>

321
00:21:31,326 --> 00:21:34,040
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm gonna play in the plaza.
Just like you did!</font>

322
00:21:41,768 --> 00:21:44,736
<font color="#FFFFFF">The guitar! It's gone!</font>

323
00:21:44,738 --> 00:21:47,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">Somebody stole
de la Cruz's guitar!</font>

324
00:21:47,038 --> 00:21:49,342
<font color="#FFFFFF">The window's broken.
Look!</font>

325
00:21:53,747 --> 00:21:55,512
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right, who's in there?</font>

326
00:21:55,515 --> 00:21:57,349
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm sorry.
It's not what it looks like.</font>

327
00:21:57,352 --> 00:21:58,865
<font color="#FFFFFF">De la Cruz is my...</font>

328
00:21:59,951 --> 00:22:02,234
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's nobody here.</font>

329
00:22:17,671 --> 00:22:19,036
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Miguel!
<i>- Mama!</i></font>

330
00:22:19,038 --> 00:22:23,674
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miguel, come home.
Where are you, Miguel?</font>

331
00:22:26,913 --> 00:22:30,515
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Dios mio!</i>
Little boy. Are you okay?</font>

332
00:22:30,517 --> 00:22:32,231
<font color="#FFFFFF">Here. Let me help you.</font>

333
00:22:33,121 --> 00:22:34,901
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thanks. I...</font>

334
00:22:45,096 --> 00:22:47,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you mind? Whoa!</font>

335
00:23:07,953 --> 00:23:10,689
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look how big she's getting.</font>

336
00:23:13,826 --> 00:23:15,727
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dante!</font>

337
00:23:15,729 --> 00:23:18,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can see me? Wait!</font>

338
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:21,781
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's going on? Dante!</font>

339
00:23:23,671 --> 00:23:25,969
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- Miguel?</font>

340
00:23:25,971 --> 00:23:27,755
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Miguel?
- Miguel?</font>

341
00:23:31,143 --> 00:23:34,845
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're here? Here, here.
And you can see us?</font>

342
00:23:34,846 --> 00:23:37,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our Migueli-ti-ti-ti-to!</font>

343
00:23:37,482 --> 00:23:38,983
<font color="#FFFFFF">Remind me how I know you.</font>

344
00:23:38,986 --> 00:23:41,968
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're your family, <i>mijo.</i></font>

345
00:23:42,923 --> 00:23:45,772
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>- Tia</i> Rosita?
<i>- Si.</i></font>

346
00:23:47,661 --> 00:23:49,942
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>- Papa</i> Julio?
<i>- Hola.</i></font>

347
00:23:50,697 --> 00:23:52,130
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Tia</i> Victoria?</font>

348
00:23:52,132 --> 00:23:54,631
<font color="#FFFFFF">He doesn't
seem entirely dead.</font>

349
00:23:54,634 --> 00:23:57,535
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's not quite alive either.</font>

350
00:23:57,538 --> 00:24:00,137
<font color="#FFFFFF">We need <i>Mama</i> Imelda.
She'll know how to fix this.</font>

351
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:04,141
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Oye!</i> It's <i>Mama</i> Imelda.</font>

352
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:05,542
<font color="#FFFFFF">She couldn't cross over.</font>

353
00:24:05,546 --> 00:24:07,978
<font color="#FFFFFF">- She's stuck!
- On the other side!</font>

354
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:10,781
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>Tio</i> Oscar? <i>Tio</i> Felipe?</font>

355
00:24:10,784 --> 00:24:12,883
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh. Hey, Miguel.</font>

356
00:24:12,884 --> 00:24:15,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have a feeling this has
something to do with you.</font>

357
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:17,654
<font color="#FFFFFF">But if <i>Mama</i> Imelda
can't come to us...</font>

358
00:24:17,656 --> 00:24:19,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then we are going to her.
<i>Vamonos!</i></font>

359
00:24:33,838 --> 00:24:35,205
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whoa.</font>

360
00:24:35,209 --> 00:24:37,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, Miguel.
It's okay.</font>

361
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:55,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dante? Dante!
Dante, wait up!</font>

362
00:24:57,564 --> 00:25:02,414
<font color="#FFFFFF">You got to stay with me, boy.
We don't know... where...</font>

363
00:25:22,823 --> 00:25:26,256
<font color="#FFFFFF">This isn't a dream then.
You're all really out there.</font>

364
00:25:26,259 --> 00:25:28,226
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You thought we weren't?
- Well, I don't know.</font>

365
00:25:28,228 --> 00:25:30,094
<font color="#FFFFFF">I thought it might've been
one of those</font>

366
00:25:30,096 --> 00:25:32,028
<font color="#FFFFFF">made up things
that adults tell kids.</font>

367
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:33,597
<font color="#FFFFFF">Like vitamins.</font>

368
00:25:33,599 --> 00:25:35,733
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miguel,
vitamins are a real thing.</font>

369
00:25:35,736 --> 00:25:37,901
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, now I'm thinking
maybe they could be.</font>

